---
import Layout from "@/layouts/main.astro"
---

<Layout>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 pt-24 pb-16 text-center">
    <div class="mx-auto mb-6 flex h-14 w-14 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-primary text-2xl text-primary-foreground">
      🔥
    </div>
    <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl text-balance">
      Open source is magic.
      <br />
      <span class="text-primary">It's also not free.</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="mx-auto mb-8 max-w-xl text-lg text-muted-foreground text-balance leading-relaxed">
      Sharing code is beautiful. Pretending the commons is self-sustaining
      doesn't help anyone. The License is a source-available license that
      lets you share your work <em>and</em> keep it viable.
      No doom, no gloom — just honest.
    </p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
      <a
        href="https://github.com/awfixer/thelicense"
        class="inline-flex h-10 items-center gap-2 rounded-xl bg-primary px-6 text-sm font-medium text-primary-foreground transition-all hover:bg-primary/90 active:scale-[0.97]"
      >
        🧑‍🌾 See the license
      </a>
      <a
        href="#how"
        class="inline-flex h-10 items-center gap-2 rounded-xl border border-border bg-card px-6 text-sm font-medium text-card-foreground transition-all hover:bg-muted active:scale-[0.97]"
      >
        Tell me more
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The problem stated warmly -->
  <section id="how" class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 pb-24">
    <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
        <div class="mb-3 text-2xl">🌱</div>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">The garden is real</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          Open source built the internet. It gave us Linux, Python, curl, and
          a million other things we take for granted. Thousands of people give
          away their best work for free because they believe in sharing. That's
          genuine and good.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
        <div class="mb-3 text-2xl">🌿</div>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">The weeds are also real</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          When everyone owns everything, nobody owns anything. Quality fragments.
          Burnout spreads. Companies extract value without returning it. This
          isn't a conspiracy — it's entropy. Every shared resource eventually
          degrades without boundaries.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6 text-center">
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed max-w-lg mx-auto">
        <strong class="text-foreground">The takeaway isn't "open source is bad."</strong>
        <br />
        It's "let's be honest about the physics of shared resources so we can
        build things that last."
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The License as solution -->
  <section class="bg-primary/5 border-y border-primary/10">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 py-20">
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="mb-4 inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-primary/10 px-4 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium text-primary">
          🛡️ The License
        </div>
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl text-balance">
          Share your work.
          <br />
          Keep your options open.
        </h2>
        <p class="mx-auto mb-10 max-w-xl text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          The AWFixer Source Available License is a practical middle ground
          between "do whatever you want" and "you can't even look at it."
          People can see your code, learn from it, use it personally
          — they just can't build a competing business on your back
          without paying for a commercial license.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-5">
          <div class="mb-2 text-xl">👀</div>
          <h3 class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold">Source available</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Anyone can read, evaluate, and learn from your code. Transparency
            isn't the enemy — it's the point.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-5">
          <div class="mb-2 text-xl">🧑‍💻</div>
          <h3 class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold">Personal use, free</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Individuals and small teams (under 10 people or $2M revenue) get
            full internal use. No license fee. No paperwork.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-5">
          <div class="mb-2 text-xl">⏳</div>
          <h3 class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold">Four years → AGPL</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            After four years the license auto-converts to AGPL-3.0. Your code
            eventually joins the open source commons — on your schedule.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Grace period highlight -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 py-20">
    <div class="rounded-2xl border-2 border-accent/30 bg-accent/5 p-8 text-center">
      <div class="mb-3 text-3xl">🌱</div>
      <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Growing? No problem.</h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mb-4 max-w-lg text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
        If you're a small team that outgrows the personal-use threshold, you
        get a <strong class="text-foreground">180-day grace period</strong> to
        sort out a commercial license. No lawsuits. No surprises.
        Just a handshake and a reasonable timeline.
      </p>
      <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">
        We want you to succeed. We just ask that success includes the people
        who built the tools you're standing on.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ-ish / Tone -->
  <section class="bg-muted/50 border-y border-border/50">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-lg text-center">
        <h2 class="mb-6 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">This isn't a crusade</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-left text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            <strong class="text-foreground">Are you anti-open-source?</strong>
            <br />
            Nope. We contribute to open source. We love open source. We just
            think the <em>only</em> model — "give it all away forever,
            no questions asked" — isn't the <em>only</em> model.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong class="text-foreground">Is this about AI?</strong>
            <br />
            Partly. The license explicitly restricts AI training on your code
            without permission. If you want your work to stay out of training
            pipelines, this gives you a legal basis to say no.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong class="text-foreground">Is this a corporation thing?</strong>
            <br />
            Not really. It's for anyone who wants to share sustainably.
            Solo devs. Small teams. Open source projects that want a
            commercial option without changing their whole identity.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong class="text-foreground">Can I use this for my project?</strong>
            <br />
            Absolutely. The license text is right there in the repo. Fork it,
            adapt it, use it. We'd love to know what you think.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 py-20 text-center">
    <div class="mb-4 text-3xl">☕</div>
    <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">
      Pull requests welcome
    </h2>
    <p class="mx-auto mb-6 max-w-md text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
      Eye rolls also welcome, but less useful. The license is a living
      document — help us make it better.
    </p>
    <a
      href="https://github.com/awfixer/thelicense"
      class="inline-flex h-10 items-center gap-2 rounded-xl bg-primary px-6 text-sm font-medium text-primary-foreground transition-all hover:bg-primary/90 active:scale-[0.97]"
    >
      🐙 View on GitHub
    </a>
  </section>
</Layout>
